<br>
     Aerimus said: &quot;As far as there being no balance here well wizards are good at killing by suprise. You might say that this is balanced by something of a disadvantage vs a prepared oponent.&quot;<br>
<br>
     It is VERY rare that I am suprised I was attacked. If you are usually suprised by and unprepared for pvp, you are some sort of ignorant sucker, and deserve to lose some gear.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/02 10:37:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> The point is, even if you know there is a possibility of getting manaburned when you zone into Greater Fay, there is not much you can do about it. Neither is there much you can do about gating into a group of people prepared to kill you, even if you zone in with a group, various zoning times make you don't all zone in at the same time and come in scattered, thus getting 'ambushed'.<br>
<br>
I think that surviving an ambush is a good enough PvP feat as it is... yet is it worth any points on SZ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udarkudaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>darkudaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/02 3:01:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Those damn underpowered wizzies. *warning short log file</span><hr size=1>  You say epic wiz with sunstrike and lure of Ice as if it's a big deal. Wiz epics, on RZ atleast, are pretty much the norm for +55 characters. I would know, I'm 1 of only 2 non epic sorceres on the server, the other is a pk. The spells arn't really anything of note either, rather if the wizard didn't have the spells it'd be worth noting. The level difference not really a big deal also, if Aerimus was 60 would it had made a difference to the fight? As no discs were used, no it wouldn't have. Voltaic is really a good representation of the basic wiz travelling around RZ at the higher end of the game, he has probably more AA than the norm though, but then he didn't MB or crit anyway. Had your slow poisen landed aerimus, the battle could have gone the other though, agree? And hence things arn't all bad for the rogue in the wide open spaces, are they? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/02 2:04:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Those damn underpowered wizzies. *warning short log file</span><hr size=1> He would have yondered. Ah well at least I can beat up darkdestiny again...and again...and again...<br>
<br>
60 wizards are NOT underpowered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umiriai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miriai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/02 3:13:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/wblew/images/icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Those damn underpowered wizzies. *warning short log file</span><hr size=1> One encounter does not make a credible argument for class balance. <p>-----
